<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Aababba Habib-Vallon Zek</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-18 16:48:52</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>There are two centaurs that drop this bow.  Coloth Meadowgreen is one (much more commanly seen, and has Magic Resistance out the ass) the other is Koldir<or something close> Thunerhoof who seems to have a higher drop rate on it.  The bow is not as good as the Raincaller, but only for Rangers.  Raincaller is ranger only, and the only reason it is better is because it adds stats in the range slot and allows you to keep a bow equipped.  The fire charges on Raincaller are nice, but dont expect them to last long.  This is the best known bow in the game that can be used by other archary classes.<BR>
<BR>
I have killed him twice in three days (the runt centaur) and both times he has dropped the bow.  Lucky me.<BR>
<BR>
